OL,4,CSNP's high taxes, says Sir Tom Hunter
OL,6,FThe SNP has previously pointed to
OL,7,FIreland as an example of what Scotland
OL,8,Fcould like be with the powers of
OL,9,Findependence.
OL,11,FBut Sir Tom said he takes a different
OL,12,Fview: "I think Scotland is one of the
OL,13,Fmost devolved nations in the world and
OL,14,Fwe have not made enough of our
OL,15,Fdevolved powers.
OL,17,F"Everybody says 'Oh, Thomas, you for
OL,18,For against independence?'
